Plot Code

rm(list=ls())
library(Rcpp)
library(ggpubr)

source("/net/mulan/disk2/jiaqiang/kdc/code/v5/kdc.R")
source("/net/mulan/disk2/jiaqiang/SDE/mulan_temp/common_function/freq_func.R")
source("/net/mulan/disk2/jiaqiang/SDE/mulan_temp/common_function/simple_plot.R")

outpath = "/net/mulan/disk2/jiaqiang/kdc/experiment/realdata/hdst/output/"
respath = "/net/mulan/disk2/jiaqiang/kdc/experiment/simulation/v3/result/"


itype = "HDST"
sample = c("CN13_D2","CN24_D1","CN24_E1","CN21_E2","CN21_C1","CN21_D1")

isam = 2

single_per_pval <- c()
for(iker in 1:5){
    load(paste0(outpath,"/",sample[isam],"_",itype,"_everyother_cosine",iker,"_kdc.rds"))
    single_per_pval <- cbind(single_per_pval,res$pval)
    rm(res)
}

for(iker in 1:5){
    load(paste0(outpath,"/",sample[isam],"_",itype,"_everyother_gaus",iker,"_kdc.rds"))
    single_per_pval <- cbind(single_per_pval,res$pval)
    rm(res)
}

load(paste0(outpath,"/",sample[isam],"_",itype,"_Projection_kdc.rds"))
single_per_pval <- cbind(single_per_pval,res$pval)

kdc_pvals   <- CombinePValues(single_per_pval)
pBY         <- p.adjust(na.omit(kdc_pvals),method="BY")

load(paste0("/net/mulan/disk2/jiaqiang/kdc/experiment/realdata/hdst/data/",sample[isam],"_unmodgtf_filtered_red_ut_",itype,"_final.rds"))

idx         <- which(is.na(kdc_pvals))
if(length(idx)>0){
    sp_count    <- sp_count[-idx,]
}

sigGenes <- sp_count[pBY<0.05,]



# log normalize
norm_count <- log(sigGenes+1)
nPC = 50

pc_type = "single"

if(pc_type=="both"){
    # calculate cell, gene simultaneously, slower than prcomp
    library(irlba)
    pca.results <- irlba(A =t(norm_count), nv = nPC)
    rd <- pca.results$v
}else{
    pca.results <- prcomp(t(norm_count), scale = TRUE)
    rd <- pca.results$rotation[,1:nPC]
}


set.seed(1) # kmeans there is some randomness

# Two Clusters
numClust = 2
cl <- kmeans(rd, centers = numClust)
centers_kmeans <- c()
for(iclust in 1:length(unique(cl$cluster))){
    m <- apply(norm_count[cl$cluster==iclust,],2,mean)
    centers_kmeans <- cbind(centers_kmeans,m)
}

ct_rel  <- apply(centers_kmeans,2,relative_func)
pltdat  <- cbind.data.frame(location[,1:2],ct_rel)
colnames(pltdat) <- c("x","y",paste0("clust",1:ncol(ct_rel)))

pp      <- lapply(1:(ncol(pltdat)-2),function(x){pattern_plot_kdc(pltdat,x,main=T,pointsize=1,titlesize=2,min.pand=0.8,max.pand=1.01,opt="C")})

fig0    <- ggarrange(pp[[1]],pp[[2]],ncol=3)
print(table(cl$cluster))
## 
##  1  2 
## 13 79
rm(cl,centers_kmeans,pp)

# Three Clusters
numClust = 3
cl <- kmeans(rd, centers = numClust)
centers_kmeans <- c()
for(iclust in 1:length(unique(cl$cluster))){
    m <- apply(norm_count[cl$cluster==iclust,],2,mean)
    centers_kmeans <- cbind(centers_kmeans,m)
}

ct_rel  <- apply(centers_kmeans,2,relative_func)
pltdat  <- cbind.data.frame(location[,1:2],ct_rel)
colnames(pltdat) <- c("x","y",paste0("clust",1:ncol(ct_rel)))

pp      <- lapply(1:(ncol(pltdat)-2),function(x){pattern_plot_kdc(pltdat,x,main=T,pointsize=1,titlesize=2,min.pand=0.8,max.pand=1.01,opt="C")})
fig1    <- ggarrange(pp[[1]],pp[[2]],pp[[3]],ncol=3)
print(table(cl$cluster))
## 
##  1  2  3 
## 63 15 14
rm(cl,centers_kmeans,pp)

# Four Clusters
numClust = 4
cl <- kmeans(rd, centers = numClust)
centers_kmeans <- c()
for(iclust in 1:length(unique(cl$cluster))){
    m <- apply(norm_count[cl$cluster==iclust,],2,mean)
    centers_kmeans <- cbind(centers_kmeans,m)
}

ct_rel  <- apply(centers_kmeans,2,relative_func)
pltdat  <- cbind.data.frame(location[,1:2],ct_rel)
colnames(pltdat) <- c("x","y",paste0("clust",1:ncol(ct_rel)))

pp      <- lapply(1:(ncol(pltdat)-2),function(x){pattern_plot_kdc(pltdat,x,main=T,pointsize=1,titlesize=2,min.pand=0.8,max.pand=1.01,opt="C")})
fig2    <- ggarrange(pp[[1]],pp[[2]],pp[[3]],pp[[4]],ncol=3,nrow=2)
print(table(cl$cluster))
## 
##  1  2  3  4 
## 42 17  8 25
rm(cl,centers_kmeans,pp)


# Five Clusters
numClust = 5
cl <- kmeans(rd, centers = numClust)
centers_kmeans <- c()
for(iclust in 1:length(unique(cl$cluster))){
    m <- apply(norm_count[cl$cluster==iclust,],2,mean)
    centers_kmeans <- cbind(centers_kmeans,m)
}

pp      <- lapply(1:(ncol(pltdat)-2),function(x){pattern_plot_kdc(pltdat,x,main=T,pointsize=1,titlesize=2,min.pand=0.8,max.pand=1.01,opt="C")})
print(table(cl$cluster))
## 
##  1  2  3  4  5 
## 53  7  8  9 15
fig3    <- ggarrange(pp[[1]],pp[[2]],pp[[3]],pp[[4]],pp[[5]],ncol=3,nrow=2)
